Plots

mp <- ggplot(gapminder %>% filter(year %in% c(1952,2007)), 
       aes(gdpPercap, lifeExp, size = pop, colour = country)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.7) +
  scale_colour_manual(values = country_colors) +
  scale_size(range = c(2, 12)) +
  scale_x_log10() +
  facet_wrap(.~year, ncol = 5) +
  theme_dblogr(legend.position = "none") +
  labs(x = "GDP per capita", y = "life expectancy")
ggsave("Gapminder_01.png", mp, width = 6, height = 4)

Download: Gapminder bubblechart.

Animations

# gganimate example
mp <- ggplot(gapminder, aes(gdpPercap, lifeExp, size = pop, colour = country)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.7, show.legend = F) +
  scale_colour_manual(values = country_colors) +
  scale_size(range = c(2, 12)) +
  scale_x_log10() +
  facet_wrap(~continent, ncol = 5) +
  theme_dblogr() +
  # Here comes the gganimate specific bits
  labs(title = 'Year: {frame_time}', x = 'GDP per capita', y = 'life expectancy') +
  transition_time(year) +
  ease_aes('linear')
anim_save("Gapminder_04.gif", mp, width = 600, height = 400)

Download GIF: Gapminder example animation.

gg_gapminder <- function(x) {
  ggplot(x, aes(gdpPercap/1000000, lifeExp, size = pop, colour = country)) +
    geom_point(alpha = 0.7) +
    geom_text(aes(label = country), alpha = 0.7) +
    scale_colour_manual(values = country_colors) +
    scale_size(range = c(2, 12)) +
    scale_x_log10() +
    theme_dblogr(legend.position = "none") +
    labs(title = "Year: {frame_time}", y = "life expectancy",
         x = "GDP per capita (Million)") +
    transition_time(year) +
    ease_aes('linear')
}
mp <- gg_gapminder(gapminder)
anim_save("Gapminder_07.gif", mp, width = 600, height = 400)

Download GIF: Gapminder animation.

Countries

gg_gapminder <- function(mycountries) {
  x <- gapminder %>% filter(country %in% mycountries)
  ggplot(x, aes(x = gdpPercap/1000000, y = lifeExp, colour = country)) +
    geom_point(size = 3) +
    geom_line(alpha = 0.7) +
    scale_colour_manual(values = country_colors) +
    scale_x_log10() +
    theme_dblogr(legend.position = "bottom") +
    labs(title = "Year: {frame_along}", y = "life expectancy",
         x = "GDP per capita (Million)") +
    transition_reveal(year)
}
mp <- gg_gapminder("Canada")
anim_save("Gapminder_12.gif", mp, width = 600, height = 400)

Download GIF: Gapminder animation, Canada.

mp <- gg_gapminder("China")
anim_save("Gapminder_13.gif", mp, width = 600, height = 400)
